{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_109","type":"agent_message","text":"I wasn’t able to complete the fix.\n\nI verified the required GraalVM exactly with `native-image --version`, then reproduced the failure with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-netty:4.0.0`. The failure is stable and remains:\n\n`java.lang.NullPointerException` in `io.netty.util.internal.PlatformDependent0.safeConstructPutInt`\nduring `io.netty.buffer.AdaptivePoolingAllocator$Chunk.<init>()`, reached from the Bolt handshake write path.\n\nWhat I found:\n- The test harness is not applying Netty’s bundled `netty-common` / `netty-buffer` native-image metadata during this build. Only `netty-codec-base`’s generated reflect config shows up in the native-image invocation.\n- I tried the likely metadata fix paths:\n  - adding the `AdaptivePoolingAllocator` reflection entries locally,\n  - adding the relevant `netty-common` reflection entries locally,\n  - mirroring Netty’s runtime-init args in the test build.\n- None of those changed the runtime failure; the same `PlatformDependent0.safeConstructPutInt` NPE remained.\n\nI reverted the exploratory edits, so the worktree is clean.\n\nAt this point the issue looks deeper than missing reachability JSON for this library version, likely in how this harness/build picks up Netty 4.2.2 native-image support or in a Netty/GraalVM interaction for this exact stack."}}
